  "prompt": "Which type of energy produce by steam?",
  "response": "Steam is primarily used to produce **thermal energy**. When steam is generated by heating water, it transforms thermal energy into mechanical energy when it expands and drives turbines or pistons. This mechanical energy can then be converted into electrical energy in power generation systems, such as steam turbines in power plants. In summary, steam is a medium that converts thermal energy into mechanical energy, which can be utilized to generate electricity or perform work.",
